SIMPLE: hunger
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hunger
<hw>Hun"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hungor</ets>; akin to OFries. <ets>hunger</ets>, D.
<ets>honger</ets>, OS. & OHG. <ets>hungar</ets>, G. <ets>hunger</ets>,
Icel. <ets>hungr</ets>, Sw. & Dan. <ets>hunger</ets>, Goth.
<ets>h<?/hrus</ets> hunger, <ets>huggrjan</ets> to hunger.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An uneasy sensation occasioned normally by the want of
food; a craving or desire for food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The sensation of hunger is usually referred to the
stomach, but is probably dependent on excitation of the sensory nerves,
both of the stomach and intestines, and perhaps also on indirect
impressions from other organs, more or less exhausted from lack of
nutriment.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any strong eager desire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O sacred <qex>hunger</qex> of ambitious minds!</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For <qex>hunger</qex> of my gold I die.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hunger</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hunger
<hw>Hun"ger</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hungered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hungering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>hungren</ets>, AS.
<ets>hyngrian</ets>. See <er>Hunger</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To feel the craving or uneasiness occasioned by want of
food; to be oppressed by hunger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have an eager desire; to long.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Blessed are they which do <qex>hunger</qex> and thirst after
righteouness.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. v. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hunger</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hunger
<hw>Hun"ger</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make hungry; to
famish.</def></p>

<p><ent>Hunger-bitten</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hunger-bit</ent>⟦br⟧
